items.title: Indians' win streak at 22 after walk-off in 10th
items.summary: The Indians rallied for one run in the ninth inning and pulled off The Streak's first walk-off in the 10th, when Jay Bruce delivered the decisive run-scoring double to seal a 3-2 victory that extended Cleveland's American League-record winning streak to 22 games. That inched the club one victory closer to the 1916 New York Giants' MLB-record run of 26 wins in a row, and trimmed the Tribe's magic number to three to clinch the AL Central crown.

items.title: Young Nats back Roark's start to beat Braves
items.summary: After the Nationals dropped the first two games of the series, manager Dusty Baker decided to give many of his regular position players a day off in order to recharge. So Baker turned to a lineup filled with his team's young talent, which provided a spark in the Nationals' 5-2 victory on Thursday night against the Braves at Nationals Park.

items.title: Phils smash 3 HRs in big 2nd to down Marlins
items.summary: The Phillies mashed their way to a three-game sweep of the Marlins on Thursday night at Citizens Bank Park.
